[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stevenage promote Darren Sarll to first-team coach role

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
New Stevenage manager Teddy Sheringham has promoted Darren Sarll from head of youth to Boro first-team coach.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 32-year-old has been coaching with Boro for the last three years, having previously worked for Brentford and Rotherham United.
Sarll has held the Uefa A Licence badge for the last 10 years.
His appointment follows that of former Colchester United midfielder Kevin Watson being named as Sheringham's assistant at Broadhall Way last week.
